graphy and life histories of men and women from the community, Nathaniel Mathews argues that the traumatic memories of the Zanzibar Revolution of 1964 are important to nation-building on both sides of the Indian Ocean.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aNationalismzTanzaniazZanzibar. 0aSwahili-speaking peopleszOmanxHistory. 0aSwahili-speaking peopleszTanzaniazZanzibarxMigrationsxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Africa / East.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520394537?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520394537423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520394537/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles